Good finishing touch. You can give it a simple print style so anyone who downloads or prints the page gets a clean one‑page reference.

```css
/* Print layout for Supportive‑Communication Toolkit */
@media print {
  body {
    background: #fff;
    color: #000;
  }

  .supportive-comm-header,
  .supportive-comm-footer,
  .supportive-comm-widget,
  .supportive-comm-toolkit {
    border: none;
    background: none;
    color: #000;
  }

  .supportive-comm-header h2 {
    color: #000;
  }

  a[href]:after {
    content: " (" attr(href) ")";
    font-size: 0.8em;
  }

  /* Collapse spacing for compact hard copy */
  .supportive-comm-header,
  .supportive-comm-footer {
    margin: 0 0 0.5em 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .supportive-comm-widget {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  /* Avoid printing navigation bars or site footers */
  nav,
  .site-footer,
  .sidebar {
    display: none !important;
  }

  /* Page break hints for long guides */
  h2, h3 {
    page-break-after: avoid;
  }
  p, ol, ul {
    page-break-inside: avoid;
  }
}
```

Put this after your main stylesheet. When printed, it removes background colors, keeps only black text, and prevents awkward page breaks, resulting in an easy‑to‑read handout while preserving the same ethical boundary messaging.
